rComments: His class is not helpful at all!! This class is an introductory course, he did not teach too much about drawing techniques. If you ask him questions, he answer is not helpful as well. Also, I handed in my final drawing assignment with my friend together. She got her marks, and the professor said he did not receive mine!!

Does not give clear advice. If you ever ask on how to improve your grade, do not expect an answer. If you don't paint the way he says, you won't get a good mark. The rubrics are so vague so it's impossible to know what he wants. He tries to be funny. He's not. Not a fun class.
Harsh professor. I had difficulty in his class and no help was given after I had asked.

Way too harsh for an introduction class. Did not learn anything from his class and he was not helpful when trying to clarify assignments. He expects you to already have the skills in painting when it's an INTRODUCTION class.
Tough!! but if you wanna challenge your art skill, go for it! your painting technique will improve at the end of the semester.
Alexander is a pretty good prof. He's engaging and gives good suggestions when you ask for help. He is a tough marker though and doesn't appreciate when you're late for class.
